      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/33/668",
      "text": [
        " «تَجْتَهِدُ رَأْيَكَ وَ تَعَمَّدُ اَلْقِبْلَةَ بِجُهْدِكَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.668 - Sama’a ibn Mehran asked Him about praying during the day or night when neither the sun, the moon, nor the stars are visible.\nImam (as) replied: \"You exert your own judgment and strive to determine the Qiblah (direction of prayer) to the best of your ability.\""
        ]
      }
